Another year, 315. Interface journalists have found on major consumer complaint websites that consumer financial companies have become a major disaster area for financial complaints. Not only are such old problems as usury, decapitation of interest, and malicious collection of collections repeatedly prohibited, new Patterns have emerged during the outbreak.

Face mask as Bait "fancy" recipients

"There is a loan company said I have been signed a mask, let me go to get it! " In the epidemic led to the critical moment of tension in protective materials, Huang Hao laments actually encountered the "Pie in the sky" good thing.

He had just received a text message showing that he had been selected in a lottery for free distribution of Pro Bono masks at Central Plain consumer finance, and that he would receive five free medical masks after registering and filling in his address.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A new user received a marketing message from Central Plain consumer finance

However, when he excitedly filled out all kinds of personal information, and registered users of the platform, but was told that the benefits can not be cashed.

More than 200,000 users have made bookings in the day and a half since the event was launched, Central Plain consumer finance said in a post on its public account the next day. Severely underestimating demand due to inadequate mask preparation. The company's first batch will be able to deliver just 20,000 masks, and only 4,000 new customers will be able to swing to the number, with subsequent masks arriving at an unspecified time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Central Plain consumer finance says 'MASKS ARE NOT READY'

"Is this a bad check to defraud personal information? " Huang Hao told the interface news reporter that he also shared with many friends and relatives to participate in the lottery to send masks activity. But in the two weeks since the event ended, not one of them has received a mask from Central Plain consumer finance.

In addition to Central Plain consumer finance, Ping An's internet-focused ping an doctor APP has also been trending on Weibo for its "free mask delivery" campaign.

It is worth mentioning that it is during the epidemic, ping an good doctor APP quietly cross the border launched ping an Puhui, 360 iou, Baidu has money to spend, small win technology and Jiufu borrowing and other lending products.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A Weibo user,@sunnymm  , received a mask from the doctor of peace

And many customers reflect, ping an good doctor sent the mask is not its original claim in the N95 mask, but goods do not plate of cotton gauze mask, N90 mask, and so on, protection standards are very different.

####The epidemic area delays the repayment difficult to fall to the ground

In addition to taking advantage of the "near-miss" of the marketing recipients of the epidemic, financial and credit policies also faced the "hard landing" dilemma during the epidemic. The interface news learned that although a number of consumer finance companies have formulated differentiated credit policies, they have exempted Hubei and non-hubei users from differential interest and fines, and reasonably delayed the repayment period, however, there are still some gaps in the implementation.

On January 31, five departments including the People's Bank of China jointly issued the notice on further strengthening financial support to prevent and control the spread of pneumonia in the COVID-19, fourteen rearranges credit reporting for some people whose loans are past due.

If, as required by the documents, the overdue credit records are adjusted reasonably, and if the persons who are hospitalized for treatment or quarantined for new pneumonia infection, the persons who are required to be quarantined for observation and the staff who participate in the prevention and control of the epidemic situation are unable to repay the loan in time due to the impact of the epidemic situation, upon confirmation by the access institution, the relevant overdue loans may be submitted without the overdue records, and the submitted loans shall be adjusted. Individuals and enterprises affected by the epidemic who have temporarily lost their sources of income may submit their credit records according to the adjusted repayment arrangements.

A relevant person in charge of a licensed consumer finance company told Interface News, "On the one hand, although companies have introduced a number of policies on Hubei's epidemic areas, they are also facing serious Information asymmetry, resulting in reduced willingness to pay, and even the phenomenon of some users evading debts without reason and maliciously. On the other hand, in Hubei, where the epidemic is serious, some consumer finance companies require users to provide proof of salary flowing from their units, notification of delayed resumption of work, etc. . Some consumer finance users are also unable to obtain the relevant certificates to enjoy preferential policies because of the complicated application procedures for extension and the inability to go out during isolation. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Suning consumer finance applied for deferment of repayment during the epidemic period

21CN poly complaint shows that Mr. Chen of Hubei said that because of isolation and closure of the city, can not provide suning finance for the epidemic area to delay the repayment of the documentary proof, after repeated negotiations failed to start to count the penalty interest.

####A & B face

In addition, the consumer finance industry has been criticized for "malicious collection" behavior during the epidemic has not disappeared.

On the 21CN complaints website, in February, a number of consumer financial clients displayed communications records showing that within a day they had received a series of calls from a call center in Chongqing, which called "death you" . In addition, a complainant showed that because one of his relatives failed to pay back on time in the immediate consumption of finance, but he received a fake "public security law" agencies to collect the text message.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A consumer finance user receives a collect call within a day of the outbreak

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
One user complained about sending threatening text messages masquerading as police officers in consumer finance

On the other side of the accusations, on the evening of March 12, jucomplainant posted an article on its wechat account saying that jucomplainant had returned 30,000 complaints against Jiexin without verification. More than 30,000 complaints pending review were related to the high interest charged by home credit. Most of the complainants'requests were for relief of arrears, refund of additional charges, etc. .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the face of 30,000 collective complaints, the collective complaints platform said: Make a substantial retreat.

In response, home credit consumer finance replied that the interface news reporter said, "We have noticed the incident and are following up on it, but do not respond at the moment. " According to our reporter's understanding, the group has returned a large number of complaints and a professional group of complainants, Laolai, through a large number of complaints pressure lending institutions, thereby achieving group non-payment.

A research report by the Zhongan Institute of Financial Science and Technology also pointed out that during the epidemic period, the overall credit risk of the credit industry may rise in the short term, and both the borrower's ability and willingness to repay will decline, this, coupled with a decline in the efficiency of institutions'post-loan management, will have an impact on the delinquency rate in the short term, in which large offline businesses may be at greater risk than small online businesses.

An analysis of the credit industry during the epidemic by Bairong Yunchuang, a third-party credit data agency, found that the number of credit reports from licensed consumers fell 10 percent in 2020 compared with the same period of the Spring Festival in 2019, but after the festival showed a rapid rise in the trend, the report pointed out that the epidemic mainly hit the offline business, for online business there is a certain positive stimulus.

However, for the more than 300 existing small and medium-sized online lending platforms, the impact of the post-spring festival epidemic is still continuing, only two weeks after the 2020 holiday to recover to about 70% of the previous year, facing a severe situation of reduced revenue and increased bad debts.

The report also highlighted that the auto financing customer base has been hit hard by the epidemic and that the pace of recovery has been severely constrained by a 40 per cent drop in post-holiday credit data calls compared with the same period last year, as auto financing operations are mainly offline purchases.

"By the end of January, overdue payments were three to four times higher than in the same period, " said a notice on Feb. 11 by Renrenjicai, a car loan platform based in Shenzhen, is a typical example of what happens to offline consumer finance.
